Subject: 1. Welcome to the Usenet Marketplace!

  Allow me to be the first to welcome you to the Usenet
    Marketplace, where anything and everything changes hands
    at better-than-average prices.  Many, many satisfied
    computer-users have purchased everything from computer
    accessories to sailboards, houses to rollerblades.
    Please use the Usenet Marketplace to your advantage.
    This series of Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs) is
    devoted to helping you through the ordeal of buying
    and selling via the Usenet.
 
  First, though, we have a few ground rules on the Usenet: 

    #1.  Before posting to any group, please read the introductory
	 articles in the newsgroup 'news.announce.newusers'.
	 There, Emily Postnews will help you through a little
	 bit of netiquette you need to know before posting.

    #2.  As a courtesy to those of us with limited disk
	 space, learn how to cancel articles BEFORE you post.
	 After your item has sold, it is courteous to issue
	 a cancel message.  Often, you need only press a
	 capital 'C' while re-reading your article, but
	 this varies from system to system.  Ask your local
	 system administrator for help.

    #3.  Every article has its place.  Pitch in! and don't
	 post articles where they don't belong.  As a rule, 
	 all misc.forsale groups are strictly non-commercial and
	 non-entrepreneurial.  Biz.marketplace, meanwhile,
	 is only for commericial and entrepreneurial ads.

     #4.  The Usenet Marketplace is serious business.  Please
	 don't post test articles, joke ads, or unrealistic
	 schemes to the Marketplace.  They will only make
	 people mad at you--and will sometimes help you lose
	 your account!  Dave Rhoades, this means you!

