Subject: 2. Purpose of the Usenet Marketplace.

  The Usenet Marketplace is a collection of roughly 40
    newsgroups, each catering to a different audience.
    Generally, misc.forsale groups are for one-of-a-kind,
    I-just-want-to-get-rid-of-it offerings by individuals.
    Biz.marketplace groups, on the other hand, are for businesses,
    services, and individuals with a profit motive.  Thus,
    if you are *reading* any of the misc.forsale groups, you
    should also read its biz.marketplace equivalent-- 
    oftentimes businesses will offer their surplus at prices
    which can't be beat!  If you are *posting*, then please
    post to exactly 1 group--the *right* one.

  Question:  "I'm a profit-motivated individual, but I
	don't get biz.marketplace at my site.  Can I post
	to misc.forsale?"
  Answer:  a loud and resounding NO!  If your site gets
	misc.forsale.*, but not biz.marketplace.*, then
	your site probably prohibits commercial use.
	Entrepreneurial use is commercial use, thus you
	shouldn't post from your site.  If you would like
	access to biz.marketplace.*, many commercial
	and free services are available.  Watch for the news
	access FAQ in the newsgroup 'news.answers'.

  Question:  "Can I post want ads to the Usenet	Marketplace?"
  Answer:  Absolutely!  Follow the same guidelines as forsale
	ads, but please be sure to include "Wanted:" in your
	subject line. 

  Question:  "If I post a chain letter, can I lose my
	account?"
  Answer:  Yes.  Very easily.  The most common chain letter
	on Usenet is the infamous "MAKE.MONEY.FAST" letter
	by Dave Rhoades.  If you see someone post this
	monstrosity, please don't respond with another post.
	Instead, send a complaint to the poster's system
	administrator. 

